creator: Department of Education (Queensland)
descriptionHtml:
QParents is a secure portal that provides parents of Queensland State School students with a new and exciting way of connecting with their school. Join the thousands of parents who have already registered to gain 24-hour direct access to your student’s information and communicate with your school easily and efficiently.
Don’t have time to go in to the school and pay for next week’s excursion?
Like to know whether the kids have swimming today?
Have a family holiday coming up and need to let the school know you’ll be away?
Need to report a new medical condition for your child as soon as possible?
With the QParents portal, you have access to everything you need to know via a single, clear student dashboard, including:
• Student Timetable
• School attendance records
• School behaviour records
• Invoices and payments
• School Report cards
• School Enrolment history
• Student school photo
You can also request updates or changes to student details using QParents, such as:
• providing reasons for past unexplained absences
• advising the school of future absences
• notifying the school of changes to student address, date of birth, and medical conditions
• viewing, selecting and paying outstanding invoices
Use QParents to manage all of your children’s details from one convenient location by adding all the students in your family to one QParents account. Don’t hesitate, register now and become a QParent!
Please note that parents can only view student information using the QParents app if their student attends a school that has joined the QParents program. Parents will be invited to register for QParents by school administration once the program has been rolled out at the school. Visit our website for support and further information about signing up for QParents.
descriptionShort: QParents is a fast, secure way for parents to access their student information.

appDetails.recentChangesHtml: Minor bug fixes and technical updates to improve performance.
